	- arbitrary sized RAM area for every player malloc'ed when WPC system is initialized
	- size defined in ROM with reference at ^SIZE_PLAYER_DATA
	- data start at offset 37 in player mem data


.WPC Heap.

- heap grows upward, stack grows downward into free RAM area
- pointer to heap in ROM (^HEAP_START: =BOTTOM_OF_HEAP)
- pointer to current start of free heap in RAM (^FREE_RAM)
- malloc:
	LDX 	^FREE_RAM
	STX 	^allocated_RAM
	LEAX	MALLOC_BYTES,X
	STX     ^FREE_RAM
- allocated RAM cannot be freed

